# ============================================================================
# Kuraka framework — gitignore
# ============================================================================
# This repo holds the portable Kuraka system. It is NOT the backup of any
# specific project's code/docs — it's the reusable framework that mounts
# into any project via mount-kuraka.sh.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exclude mirrors of sie_v2 (synced to this vault but not part of framework).
# Use /-prefixed paths so we only match the top-level dirs — NOT the same-named
# subdirs inside kuraka-artifacts/ which ARE part of the framework.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/docs/
/documentacion-backend/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Exclude project-specific rules 01-15 (these are team conventions of sie_v2,
# not universal Kuraka rules). Only 16-agent-backup and 17-kuraka-token-
# optimizations are the personal meta-rules of the Kuraka system itself.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
rules/01-*.md
rules/02-*.md
rules/03-*.md
rules/04-*.md
rules/05-*.md
rules/06-*.md
rules/07-*.md
rules/08-*.md
rules/09-*.md
rules/10-*.md
rules/11-*.md
rules/12-*.md
rules/13-*.md
rules/14-*.md
rules/15-*.md

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS / editors / caches
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Central project store (unified layout). projects/<slug>/ holds ALL per-project
# Kuraka data: registry.md, layer/ (.claude/project snapshot), state/ (docs/process
# snapshot), cycles/ (RETRO+telemetry) and backup.yaml. projects/INDEX.md is the
# regenerated cross-project catalog. By project decision this store is
# filesystem-only (NOT versioned): the WHOLE projects/ store is ignored. It
# survives solution branch switches via the central copy and is restored by
# kuraka-restore.py; it is not pushed with the vault.
# (cycle-archive/ and projects-docs/ were merged into projects/<slug>/.)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
/projects
